&lt;p&gt;Driving accuracy. Supporting strong financial operations. —&lt;strong&gt; Join Velocity Electronics as our next ACCOUNTANT in Austin, TX.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;ACCOUNTANT&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;AUSTIN, TX &lt;/strong&gt;to perform a variety of accounting functions&amp;nbsp;to deliver exceptional experiences and outcomes. The functions include month-end close processes, financial statement preparation, balance sheet reconciliations, fixed asset accounting, compiling data for tax filings and other responsibilities. Activities will be carried out in multiple countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are detail-oriented and enjoy working in a collaborative finance environment that supports the business through reliable financial processes — we want to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What can you expect to do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Month-End Close:&lt;/strong&gt; Perform month-end close duties while ensuring adherence to internal deadlines, company policies, and applicable accounting standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tax Filings:&lt;/strong&gt; Complete activities associated with tax filings as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Operations Support:&lt;/strong&gt; Support accounts receivable, accounts payable, and expense report processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Training:&lt;/strong&gt; Assist in training team members as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt; Assist in the preparation of timely and accurate monthly accrual-based financial statements and support schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Reconciliations:&lt;/strong&gt; Prepare account reconciliations, including identification and resolution of discrepancies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Audit Support:&lt;/strong&gt; Assist in responding to year-end external audit inquiries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accounting Compliance:&lt;/strong&gt; Seek management guidance to ensure all transactions are recorded appropriately in accordance with accounting standards and accurately reflect the activity and purpose of each account.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Credit Management Support&lt;/strong&gt;: Provide assistance with tasks related to establishing credit limits for new and existing business partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is the experience and knowledge needed to be successful in this role?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in accounting or a related field; an advanced degree and/or active CPA license is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in general ledger accounting and financial reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in operational accounting and accounting services (AR, AP, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to handle sensitive and confidential information with discretion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong computer skills; experience with complex ERP systems is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Velocity Electronics, our core values—Be Amazing Today, Demonstrate Mutual Respect and Trust, Act Courageously, and Own Your Outcomes—drive our success. Are you someone who thrives in a fast-paced environment and is driven to exceed goals? At Velocity, you’ll be empowered to take ownership of your success, build meaningful relationships, and drive growth through innovative solutions. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join a top independent electronic components distributor serving the world’s leading contract manufacturers and OEMs! &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Connecting with Customers Enabling Business Growth. —&amp;nbsp; We are seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Business Development Manage (BDM) in Germany,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to oversee key customer accounts and drive business opportunities that support sustainable, long-term growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for identifying, developing, and strengthening business opportunities by building and nurturing strong, strategic partnerships with customers. If you’re driven to build trusted customer partnerships that create value and drive sustainable growth —we want to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What can you expect to do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Development &amp;amp; Customer Relationship Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive expansion of Velocity’s market share by strengthening relationships with existing customers and developing new client opportunities.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Thinking &amp;amp; Opportunity Identification: &lt;/strong&gt;Identify, develop, and implement strategic business opportunities through value-added programs that enhance customer partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Growth Strategy &amp;amp; Results Orientation: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead initiatives focused on achieving sustainable and strategic customer growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Analysis &amp;amp; Strategic Planning: &lt;/strong&gt;Evaluate and identify key growth opportunities, partnering with leadership to establish and execute strategic growth plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership &amp;amp; Coaching: &lt;/strong&gt;Collaborate with Sales Management to support, guide, and help develop Strategic Account Managers to optimize sales performance and profitability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Negotiation &amp;amp; Stakeholder Influence: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead initiatives aimed at securing Approved Vendor status with multinational customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration: &lt;/strong&gt;Partner with leadership to ensure alignment between top-down corporate strategies and bottom-up market insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Engagement &amp;amp; Relationship Building: &lt;/strong&gt;Develop customer engagement strategies and participate in regular client visits alongside Strategic Account Managers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Accountability &amp;amp; Organizational Skills: &lt;/strong&gt;Prepare and maintain regular reports summarizing travel expenses associated with customer visits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Analysis &amp;amp; Business Reporting: &lt;/strong&gt;Develop and present periodic performance reports, including sales forecasts, gross profit projections, regional work plans, and performance results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication &amp;amp; Cultural Alignment: &lt;/strong&gt;Act as a brand ambassador by promoting and communicating Velocity’s culture, core values, and value proposition to customers and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is the experience and knowledge needed to be successful in this role?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4-year college degree in a sales related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of sales or business development experience in the electronic components industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated expertise in sourcing, account management, CRM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Substantial product knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Required Languages: Dutch, English (both required).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferred Languages: French.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
